{"lemma":"فَلِّ","slug":"فَلِّ","root":"ف.ل.ل","root_slug":"ف-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n34418","n34419","n34420"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to notch, to nick","examples":[{"text":"وَائِل بَعْضُهُمْ يَقْتُلُ بَعْضًا لَا يَفُلُّ ٱلْحَدِيدُ إِلَا ٱلْحَدِيدَ .","english":"Wael tribe kill each other, won't notch iron but iron."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to break the sharpness of, to defeat, to rout"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have notches, to fell"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to run away, to break free (cf. فَرَّ (farra))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَلَّ (falla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"notch, nick, incision"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"piece broken off because of notching, fragment, sliver, filing, spark and the like"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"meagre remnant, piece of rubble"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a company of men detached or broken off after the defeat of the rest, a party of fugitives"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"land where there is no herbage, destitute region"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"devoid, destitute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Arabian jasmine (Jasminum sambac)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cork, the bast of the cork oak"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Perhaps cognate to Hindi फूल (phūl, “flower”).\n\nFrom Ancient Greek φελλός (phellós, “cork”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34418","headword_ar":"فَلٌّ","root":"fl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A break,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"notch, in the edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, T, S, M, O, Msb, K,) of a sword, (ISk, T, S, O, Msb, K,) [or the like,] or of anything; (M;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~apN","text_ar":"فَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single break,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"notch, in the edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a sword: (TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwlN","text_ar":"فُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, T, S, M, O, Msb, K,) of which an ex. occurs in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoda","text_ar":"بَيْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, TA:) it has been said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwlN","text_ar":"فُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n.; but it is more correctly said to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~N","text_ar":"فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion that has fallen off from a thing, like the filings of gold and of silver, and the sparks of fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwlN","text_ar":"فُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA) of men; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faliylN","text_ar":"فَلِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K, TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwlN","text_ar":"فُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  And it is [an epithet] applied to a number of men, (S, M, O, K, [in the CK in this case, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ful~N","text_ar":"فُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and to a single man, (S, O,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Defeated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ful~aY","text_ar":"فُلَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies thus, applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katiybap","text_ar":"كَتِيبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. a military force, or troop, &c.]; (AA, T, O, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fur~aY","text_ar":"فُرَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, T, O:) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN fal~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN fal~N","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and sometimes [when speaking of a number of men] they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwlN","text_ar":"فُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filaAlN","text_ar":"فِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O;) accord. to the copies of the K, the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwlN","text_ar":"فُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afolaAlN","text_ar":"اَفْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but correctly the latter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ful~aAlN","text_ar":"فُلَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rum~aAnN","text_ar":"رُمَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the M; (TA;) [i. e.] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwlN","text_ar":"فُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ful~aAlN","text_ar":"فُلَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~N","text_ar":"فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in a pl. sense it is said that] it must be either a quasi-pl. n. or [originally] an inf. n.: if the former, the sing. should by rule be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAl~N","text_ar":"فَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the case being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arobN","text_ar":"شَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [of which the former is a sing, and the latter is a quasi-pl. n.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAl~N","text_ar":"فَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flwl","text_ar":"فلول"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not necessarily pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~N","text_ar":"فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but is rather pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAl~N","text_ar":"فَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for the pl. of the quasi-pl. n. is extr., like the pl. of the pl.: (M, TA: *) and as to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~aAlN","text_ar":"فَلَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is necessarily pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAl~N","text_ar":"فَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolN","text_ar":"فَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not of the forms that have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuE~aAlN","text_ar":"فُعَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the measure of a pl.: (M, TA:) if it [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~N","text_ar":"فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] be [originally] an inf. n., [this accounts for its being applied alike to a number of men and to a single man, which is not mentioned in the M, or] it is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasojN","text_ar":"نَسْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manosuwjN","text_ar":"مَنْسُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasoju Alyamani","text_ar":"نَسْجُ اليَمَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)       -A4-  Also Land"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected with drought"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barrenness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fil~N","text_ar":"فِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": or [i. e. the former accord. to the K, but app. each accord. to the text of the M as given in the TT,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is rained upon but does not produce plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as the rain has failed to fall upon during several years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is not rained upon between two lands that have been rained upon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or, accord. to AO, this is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTiyTapN","text_ar":"خَطِيطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fl~","text_ar":"فلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"having the second of the meanings expl. in this sentence: (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or upon which rain has not fallen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [in this sense, in the TT, as from the T, written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fil","text_ar":"فِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fil~","text_ar":"فِلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and so in the same, as from the T and M, in the sense here following:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is nothing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, * K; *) so says IAar; whence, he adds,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfalaApu","text_ar":"الفَلَاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but [Az says] I do not think that it is taken thence: (T:) the pl. is like the sing., [or rather the word used as a sing. is likewise used as a pl.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afolaAlN","text_ar":"اَفْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) this pl. form being sometimes used: (M:) or the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfil~u","text_ar":"الفِلُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afolaAlN","text_ar":"اَفْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN A^afolaAlN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ اَفْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.)       -A5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort of cloth made of the hard fibres of flax."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["ISk","T","S","M","O","Msb","K","TA","AA","AO"]},{"entry_id":"n34419","headword_ar":"فَلٌّ","root":"fl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a term for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAsamiyn muDaAEa*","text_ar":"يَاسَمِين مُضَاعَذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Double jasmine"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered so"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"either"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlt~arokiyb","text_ar":"بِالتَّرْكِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an expression meaning, as used in the present day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by grafting"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by slitting the stem thereof and inserting into it the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"additional"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jasmine"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by budding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is a flower of pure whiteness; and the rubbing oneself with its leaves perfumes the body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [this name, or, more commonly, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fil~","text_ar":"فِلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", is now applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arabian jasmine"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jasminum sambac"},{"kind":"text","text":"), or, as Forskål says (Flora Aegypt. Arab. p. cii.),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nyctanthes sambac,"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by him among the plants cultivated in El-Yemen.] ―         -b2-  [Freytag, misled by the CK, has assigned to this word a meaning belonging to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~N","text_ar":"فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34420","headword_ar":"فِلٌّ","root":"fl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Land"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no herbage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or land"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not rained upon, and in which is no herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fal~N","text_ar":"فَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaA fil~FA mina","text_ar":"غَدَا فِلًّا مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aEaAmi","text_ar":"الطَّعَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went forth early in the morning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devoid of food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fil~N","text_ar":"فِلٌّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alxayori","text_ar":"مِنَ الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a verse, (S, O,) in the poetry of 'Abd-Allah Ibn-Rawáhah and in that of Hassán, (S, O,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Devoid of good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~N","text_ar":"عَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as has become thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of hair. (K.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ful~N","text_ar":"فُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}